Cell.Text: Why are you not welcome in Dragon Bridge?
I'm just a humble Breton who used to frequent the local tavern. That was, until I met Telisha...Now I am banned from that establishment.
I'm reconsidering your offer.
Good. Would you care to hear the details?
Is your offer still on the table?
[S] G|I'm afraid you took too long to reconsider. I'll be leaving now, as I have somewhere else I need to be. I'm in quite a hurry too.
Who's Telisha?

She's a prospective merchant who works as a barmaid at the Four Shields. | She likes to gamble on games of coin toss, and take advantage of the patrons after she's served them a few drinks. | Her and I used to be on good terms...that was until she chose me as one of those said patrons.
Why were you banned?
I was banned because I was cheated out of something precious to me. | I was also falsely accused of harassment in my attempts to retrieve what was rightfully my property.
I won.
Not the response I was anticipating. Very unusual, perhaps I wasn't cheated out of my late mother's ring after all?
I lost.
Sounds about right. I knew it! I was cheated out of my late mother's ring! That wench.
I didn't play.
Good for you. If only I had resisted the temptation myself, I would not have gotten into this mess. | You see, I ended up betting my late mother's ring.
Care to know the details?
That being said, I don't care to divulge anymore details regarding my personal affairs at this point. Maybe I'll change my mind later.
<<Shared>> Alright then.
<<Shared>> Sure thing.
<<Shared>> Very well.
<<Shared>> Of course.
<<Shared>> Alright then.
<<Shared>> Sure thing.
<<Shared>> Very well.
<<Shared>> Of course.

One night, after a hard days work of transporting product for my employer, I decided to attend the Four Shields Tavern for my usual evening meal. | The day has been tough, so I decided to hit the mead hard that night. | That was when I was approached by Telisha Ria. She offered to play a game of coin toss with me. I'd seen her do it before. | Naturally, I accepted her offer. Ahh yes...the thrill of the chase, well, the next thing I knew, I'd lost all of my gold. | I was suffering sunken losses, and my judgement was impaired, so I threw caution to the wind...I bet my late mother's ring.

Let's talk business then. | My late mother's ring is locked away in The Four Shields Tavern by Telisha Ria - She cheated me out of it. | I want you to retrieve it and bring it back to me in the Winking Skeever. | You will be rewarded and I promise I will make it worth your time. Do we have a deal?
How foolish of you.

I know, it was foolish of me. I lost it of course. I am not one for owning many possessions, nor is it an extravagant or valuable piece of jewellery. | It simply has a great sentimental value to me. | What's concerning is that Telisha travels to Solitude often, so it's only a matter of time before she sells it. | Also, I believe I may have been slighted by that woman. I have my suspicions as to how she did it, but I will not utter them until I am certain. | Seeing as I am no longer welcome in town, could I ask that you retrieve my ring for me? I will make it worth your while.
I understand, we all have our vices.

Yes. But I don't expect any sympathy from you. I'm responsible for my own actions, and I'll pay for them in due course. | That ring is all I have left of my mother, and she entrusted it to me shortly before she passed away. | Seeing as how I cannot correct this mistake on my own, may I ask for your help with this predicament? I promise I will make it worth your while.
What are your terms?

I will pay you once you retrieve it, and then return it to me in The Winking Skeever. | Also, it's likely Telisha is keeping it locked away with a number of other valuables... | Should you take anything, I am willing to turn a blind eye to such indiscretions. What do you say?
Sure. We have a deal.

[S] G|Thank you! This means a lot to me. I'm really going out on a limb here by trusting you, so I promise your efforts will be rewarded handsomely. | Well, now I have you on the job, I'm headed straight to the Skeever for a drink. See you when you're done.
I'm not interested.
[S] G|Very well. I'll give you until this time tomorrow to reconsider. | Please come and see me If you change your mind. I'm not going anywhere for now, so you'll know where to find me.
I'm not interested.
G|I see. Please recall there is a time limit on my offer, so come and see me as soon as you can if you change your mind.
Do you have anything for sale?
Not officially you could say. Well, I need a drink, how about you?
Do you have any more wine?
[S] Sure do. First bottles free. The next one is going to cost you 150 gold. What can I say? I am an enterprising individual.
Do you have any more wine?
Yes. Would you like another bottle? That'll be 150 gold.
Do you have any more wine?
[S] Why yes I do! I just restocked. Would you like another bottle?
Do you have any more wine?
G|Unfortunately, I'm all out. I restock upon daybreak every Middas though, assuming I haven't sold out. | Come and see me again when you're ready.
Sure thing.
[S] G|Here you go.
I don't have enough gold.
G|Oh well, that's a shame. Come and see me when you have enough gold.
No thank you.
G|Maybe next time then?
Is that your dog?

Yes, his name is Halvar. He's very friendly. The townsfolk don't mind having him around, wish you could say the same thing about me though. | We do everything together, I wouldn't have it any other way. He's my best friend, and he's been there for me since he was a pup. | I'm of the opinion that it's nature's greatest crime - having their lives be shorter than men that is.
What type of wine was that?
S|That was Firebrand wine my friend. Very rare in these parts. I can get it easily though. Enough said, or I may get myself into some trouble.
Where do you get your wine from?
S|Ahhh...that's privileged information. Perhaps if you do something for me, I'll let you in on the big secret.
Telisha? Yes, I've met her.
I see. What happened? Did you win, lose, or not gamble at all?
[S] I might know a thing or two about that...
[S] Well, you could say I know a little...
[S] Let's say I do. It's gonna cost you...
